Usermod : usermod command or modify user is a command in Unix
that is used to change the
properties of a user in Unix through the command line.
sudo usermod -c "comment" name:To add a comment for a user
sudo usermod -d /home/dir_name name :To change the home
directory of a user sudo usermod -e
yyyy-mm-dd test_user: To change the expiry date of a user sudo
usermod -L test_user :To lock a user
sudo usermod -U test_user :To Unlock a user
