Chage : The chage command is used to view and change the user
password expiry information. This command is used when the login
is to be provided for a user for a limited amount of time or when it is
necessary to change the login password from time to time
Chfn : chfn modifies a user's "finger" information. This information
is stored in the file /etc/passwd, and
